      <exercise workspace="1.3in" category="essential">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Without changing their meanings, convert each of the following sentences into a sentence having the form <q>If <m>p</m>, then <m>q</m></q>.
          </p>

          <p>
            <ol cols="1" marker="(a)">
              <li>
                A matrix is invertible provided its determinant is non-zero.
              </li>
              <li>
                A function is rational if it is a polynomial.
              </li>
              <li>
                An integer is divisible by 8 only if it is divisible by 4.
              </li>
              <li>
                A series converges whenever it converges absolutely.
              </li>
              <li>
                A function is integrable provided the function is continuous.
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>

        <solution>
          <p>
            <ol marker="(a)">
              <li>
                <p>
                  There are multiple correct ways to rewrite this sentence. Here are a few examples:
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p>
                        If its determinant is not zero, then a matrix is invertible.
                      </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <p>
                        If a matrix has determinant that is not zero, then it is invertible.
                      </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <p>
                        If a matrix has nonzero determinant, then it is invertible.
                      </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <p>
                        If a matrix has nonzero determinant, then the given matrix is invertible.
                      </p>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  There are multiple correct ways to rewrite this sentence. One example is <q>If a function is a polynomial, then it is rational.</q>
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  If an integer is divisible by 4, then it is divisible by 8.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  If a series converges absolutely, then it converges.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  If a function is continuous, then it is integrable.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </solution>

