            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>

      <solution>
        <p>
          <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li>
                    <title>Converse:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>5 \nmod x</m> and <m>5 \nmod y</m>, then <m>5 \nmod xy</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Contrapositive:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>5 \divides x</m> or <m>5 \divides y</m>, then <m>5 \divides xy</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Inverse:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>5 \divides xy</m> then <m>5 \divides x</m> or <m>5 \divides y</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li>
                    <title>Converse:</title>
                    <p>
                      If <m>y \leq x</m> then <m>y^3 + yx^2 \leq x^3 + xy^2</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Contrapositive:</title>
                    <p>
                      If <m>y \gt x</m> then <m>y^3 + yx^2 > x^3 + xy^2</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Inverse:</title>
                    <p>
                      If <m>y^3 + yx^2 > x^3 + xy^2</m> then <m>y \gt x</m>.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                <dl>
                  <li>
                    <title>Converse:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>x</m> is odd, then <m>7x + 9</m> is even.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Contrapositive:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>x</m>is even, then <m>7x + 9</m> is odd.
                    </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <title>Inverse:</title>

                    <p>
                      If <m>7x + 9</m> is odd, then <m>x</m> is even.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </dl>
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </solution>

